wikipedia_page.main: Walter Mooney (c. 1892 – c. 1958) was an English professional rugby league footballer who played in the 1910s and 1920s. He played at representative level for Great Britain, and at club level for Leigh (Heritage № 214) (captain), as a stand-off, i.e. number 6.

response: The Singapore Free Press and Mercantile Advertiser (1884-1942), 14 April 1924, Page 12 details the squad as including; T. Howley, W. Mooney, and D. Rees. The photograph entitled 'Great Britain Rugby League Touring Team - Australasia 1924' shows four people named ??, one in casual clothing (D Murray; a coach/physio/trainer?), and three in playing kit, these are very likley to be; Tommy Howley, Walter Mooney, and Dai Rees, but not necessarily seated in that order.
* Walter Mooney won caps for Great Britain while at Leigh in 1924 against New Zealand (2 matches)
